.row
  .span4.cta-box
    = image_tag 'doghouse.png', class: 'taglineLogo'
    .main-cta
      - if @current_user
        = link_to content_tag(:i, ' Go to the app', class: 'icon-circle-arrow-right'), app_path, class: 'btn btn-large btn-primary primary-cta'
      - else
        = link_to content_tag(:i, ' Sign in with Twitter', class: 'icon-twitter'), "/auth/twitter", class: 'btn btn-large btn-info primary-cta-sign-twitter'
      = link_to content_tag(:i, ' Watch the video', class: 'icon-play-circle'), 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yDXzHiMtaqE', target: '_blank', class: "btn btn-large"
  .span8
    .hero-unit
      .hero-unitContainer
        = link_to image_tag('CloudSpokes.png', class: 'cloudspokelink'), CLOUDSPOKES_CHALLENGE_LINK, target: '_blank'
        %h1 Twitter DogHouse
        %p Social networking with Twitter is great except when the people you follow pollute your feed with sponsored spam, political flamewars, and live-tweets of some show or event you don't care about. With this app you can #{content_tag :strong, 'unfollow'} them, tell them they are being annoying, and #{content_tag :strong, 're-follow them after a specified amount of time.'}
        %p.social-links
          = link_to content_tag(:i, ' Follow @TwitDoghouse', class: 'icon-twitter'), "#{TWITTER_ROOT}/TwitDoghouse", target: '_blank', class: 'label'
          = link_to content_tag(:i, ' View on GitHub', class: 'icon-github'), 'https://github.com/dubroe/twitter-doghouse', target: '_blank', class: "label"
#howdoeswork.row
  .marketing-heading
    %h1 How does it work
    %hr
  .span4
    %h3 #{content_tag :i, nil, class: 'icon-hand-up icon-large'} Select the user
    %p Upon signing in with Twitter, you can search the people you follow and choose someone to put in your DogHouse.
  .span4
    %h3 #{content_tag :i, nil, class: 'icon-hand-down icon-large'} Add to DogHouse
    %p Specify the length of the punishment and set (optional) tweets to be sent to the user when inserting and releasing from your DogHouse.
  %div
    %h3 #{content_tag :i, nil, class: 'icon-undo icon-large'} Automatically release from DogHouse
    %p The user will be automatically re-followed after the expiration of the time that you specify.
#twittersyntax.row
  .marketing-heading.span12
    %h1 Add To Your DogHouse Right Within Twitter
    %hr
  .span6.twitter-syntax
    %h3 DogHouse tweet syntax*
    .well
      %p @TwitDoghouse #{content_tag :code, 'username'} #{content_tag :code, 'timeframe'} #{content_tag :code, 'tweet message'}
    %p #{content_tag :code, 'username'} = the person that you want to add to your DogHouse (without the @ symbol!)
    %p
      %span #{content_tag :code, 'timeframe'} = for how long do you want to keep the person in your DogHouse
      %ul.unstyled
        %li #{content_tag :code, '#m'} number of minutes
        %li #{content_tag :code, '#h'} number of hours
        %li #{content_tag :code, '#d'} number of days
    %p #{content_tag :code, 'tweet message'} = optional tweet to send to the user telling them that you've put them in your DogHouse
    %span.label.pull-right * You have to sign in once before you can use it.
  .span6
    %h3 Example:
    %p @TwitDoghouse JureStern 5d You're going in my doghouse because you are yapping too much.
    %h3 Result:
    %p The user JureStern will be unfollowed and the following tweet will be sent from your Twitter account: "@JureStern You're going in my doghouse because you are yapping too much." In 5 days JureStern will be re-followed.
    %h3 Note:
    %p It may take up to 10 minutes for your automated DogHouse insertion request to be processed.